parameters:
I don't know what kind of ritual this magic circle
is used for, but it seems like we found some
evidence.
This is a grimoire about summoning demons.

Yes, it's good that we found it before the
summoning took place.
It's unfortunate, but it's the truth.

Now, all that's left is to report to the higher-
ups.

(The mission is somehow resolved. The only
remaining issue is with Leviathan...)

I decided not to go. I sensed the presence of an
intruder in the room.

Hehe... I knew that there was someone other than
the club members in the magic research room
yesterday.

Since they're plotting such a plan, we need to be
extra cautious and stay on guard.
I never thought Elena would betray us.
I never heard that Elena would summon a demon!

If I had known, I wouldn't have cooperated from
the beginning.
That's a shame. The body was amazing though.
Now, what should we do with these guys?
Don't misunderstand, we're the ones cornering you.

Because I found evidence that you were trying to
summon a demon.
That's right. There's no need for excuses.

You guys will never leave the Magic Research Club
room.
Become the sacrifice for the summoning ritual.

If that's the case, then I'll just have to force
you out.

(The opponent is strong, but this situation is
even worse. Because right now...)

You guys just fought against a powerful
gatekeeper, didn't you?

Do you guys still have the magical power to fight
against us, members of the Magic Research Club?

The Torrent King was strong, right? I don't have
the luxury to hold back even for myself.
Even so, I will capture you and show you.

There is no chance of winning against us... That's
the reality.
Hahaha, you understand it well, don't you?

I don't want to fight and hurt Amelia
unnecessarily. Let's surrender quietly.

Your comrades are saying that, but what are you
going to do?
Because Masamune-kun is important to me too.

It's a relief that we can save some trouble. Hey,
put these guys in the cell.
By the way, about the fun part...

(I know what will happen to Amelia... but for now,
there's no other choice)
